{"comments":"Matroid Polytope for Continuous Optimization.\n\n## Theoretical Foundation\n\nThe matroid polytope P(M) for a matroid M is:\n\n  P(M) = conv{1_I : I independent in M}\n       = {x ∈ [0,1]^n : x(S) ≤ r(S) for all S ⊆ V}\n\nWhere r(S) is the rank function of the matroid.\n\n## Key Property\n\nLinear optimization over P(M) reduces to greedy selection on the matroid.\nThis is the foundation of the continuous greedy algorithm.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Continuous.FractionalSolution\n- Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Types (Matroid, GroundSet)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["matroid",{"annotation":[],"contents":"m","tag":"TypeVar"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["groundSet",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","GroundSet"],"GroundSet"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[83,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Continuous/MatroidPolytope.purs","start":[80,29]},"title":"MatroidPolytope"}],"comments":"The matroid polytope P(M) for a matroid M.\n\nP(M) = conv{1_I : I independent in M}\n     = {x ∈ [0,1]^n : x(S) ≤ r(S) for all S ⊆ V}\n\nKey property: linear optimization over P(M) reduces to greedy.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":["Representational","Phantom"],"typeArguments":[["m",null],["v",null]]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[83,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Continuous/MatroidPolytope.purs","start":[80,1]},"title":"MatroidPolytope"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create matroid polytope.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],